body: "GH-607. A structurally-unparseable item .toon (e.g. count header disagreeing with data lines — exactly what a botched concurrent-append merge produces, pm-9q2t) is silently skipped by pm validate: ok:true, checked_items:0, while pm get on the same item exits 1 \"TOON item document is not valid TOON\". The workspace-integrity command must fail on provably unreadable items; checked_items vs on-disk file-count mismatch is itself a failure. Related counts-only precedent pm-a9mc."
